# CourtLedger — Club Doubles League

A single-file static site, same idea as your World Cup sweepstake: it runs entirely
from a free GitHub repo, no Firebase and no server. League data lives in
`docs/data.json`. The browser reads it on load; an admin (anyone holding a token)
writes results straight back to the repo via the GitHub API.

## What it does

- Multiple leagues running at once (selector chips at the top).
- Admin enters players, then **randomises** or **manually picks** the pairs.
  Pairs stay fixed for the league.
- Single round robin generated automatically (every team plays every other once).
- Each fixture is **exactly three games**. Anyone with the link enters all three
  game scores; the league table derives itself.
- **Scoring:** 1 league point per *game* won — so a fixture ends 3–0 (3 pts vs 0)
  or 2–1 (2 pts vs 1).
  **Tiebreak: total points scored across all games** — an 11–9 loss still banks
  those 9 points toward the tiebreak, then point difference, then games won.
- Run separate leagues for **Mixed** and **Mens** just by naming them
  (e.g. "Mixed Doubles — Autumn 2026", "Mens Doubles — Autumn 2026"). Each league
  is fully independent — its own teams, fixtures, and table.
- Mark a league **complete** when the season ends (it greys out but stays visible).

## Setup (about 10 minutes — same flow as the sweepstake)

1. **Create the repo** — github.com → New repository → name it `pickleball-league`,
   set **Public** → Create.
2. **Edit two lines** in `docs/index.html` near the top of the `<script>`:
   ```js
   const REPO_OWNER = "YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME";   // your username
   const REPO_NAME  = "pickleball-league";      // match the repo name
   ```
3. **Upload the files** — drag the contents of this folder into the repo
   (`docs/index.html`, `docs/data.json`, `README.md`) → Commit.
4. **Enable Pages** — Settings → Pages → Source: Deploy from a branch →
   branch `main`, folder `/docs` → Save.
5. **Make an admin token** — GitHub → Settings → Developer settings →
   Fine-grained tokens → Generate new token. Scope it to **only this repo**,
   permission **Contents: Read and write**. Copy it.
6. **Share the link** — `https://YOURUSERNAME.github.io/pickleball-league/`.
   Players just open it and enter results. No token needed to enter scores.

## Running a league (admin)

1. Open the site → **Admin** (top right) → paste your token → Unlock.
   The token lives only in that browser tab (sessionStorage), never in the repo.
2. **+ New league** → name it, paste players one per line (even number, 4+).
3. **Pair teams** → 🎲 Randomise, or pick pairs from the dropdowns → Create.
4. Done. Share the link; players enter their own results.

## A note on the trade-off you chose

To keep this a pure static site with no server, the admin token sits in the
browser tab while you're signed in as admin. Scoped to **Contents on this one
repo**, the worst anyone could do is edit pickleball scores in this repo — and
every change is in git history, so any bad edit reverts in seconds. That's the
deal you accepted for an internal club tool; it would not be appropriate for
anything sensitive.

If you ever want it locked down properly, the upgrade is a ~30-line Cloudflare
Worker holding the token server-side — the front end stays identical.
